Package: rfsnEfficiency
Title: Risk-Reduction Efficacy and Efficiency of Risk-Management Configurations
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Francis", "Tsiboe", email = "ftsiboe@hotmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A general, on-demand toolkit for evaluating risk-management or
    safety-net configurations. From user-supplied end-of-season outcome draws
    (ideally one element per agent) and program parameters (cost, premium,
    subsidy, and an indemnification rule that may be a function), it builds a
    configurable outcome (revenue, profit, margin, or a custom / cost-side
    measure) relative to a no-program baseline and computes efficacy scores
    (mean lift, variability reduction) and a risk-reduction efficiency ratio,
    with comparisons across regimes or scenarios. Implements the
    risk-reduction-efficiency metric of Tsiboe et al. (2025).
License: GPL (>= 3)
